De-spin weights which were attached to

00:10:24.759 --> 00:10:29.589
the probes that were generally traveling
in the same direction as the probes

00:10:29.589 --> 00:10:36.069
themselves. In deep space the sun's power
is too weak for solar cells so all of

00:10:36.069 --> 00:10:41.170
these use radioisotope thermoelectric
generators basically the heat from a

00:10:41.170 --> 00:10:44.949
radioactive source is turned into
electrical power for the spacecraft's

00:10:44.949 --> 00:10:48.759
electrical systems and depending upon
the half-life of a radioactive material

00:10:48.759 --> 00:10:53.199
these can last for decades.
Eventually though the power from the

00:10:53.199 --> 00:10:57.429
radioactive source and the degeneration
of the bimetallic thermocouples which

00:10:57.429 --> 00:11:01.689
convert the heat into electrical power
will drop to a point where they can no

00:11:01.689 --> 00:11:06.429
longer power the craft but it's a
testament to the quality of these

00:11:06.429 --> 00:11:12.819
spacecraft and the electronic components
inside made in the 1970s with 1960s

00:11:12.819 --> 00:11:17.259
designs in some cases that they are
still working in the harsh conditions of

00:11:17.259 --> 00:11:24.189
deep space over four decades later.
Pioneer 10 launched in 1972 and stopped

00:11:24.189 --> 00:11:29.980
transmitting due to a lack of power in
2003, it's currently about 18.1

00:11:29.980 --> 00:11:34.870
billion kilometers from Earth and
in 12 kilometers a second in the general

00:11:34.870 --> 00:11:40.650
direction of the star Aldebaran 68
light-years away. Pioneer 11 launched in

00:11:40.650 --> 00:11:47.620
1973 and in 1995 due to a lack of power
